Wait until the last frost has passed to start pruning. The dead branches help protect the root systems from the frost. After the last frost date, which should happen in later April or early May depending on your area, you can take off the branches. 

You may see new spring growth happening underneath the old branches before you remove them.

If you live in the United States, you can use your ZIP code to check the expected last frost date here: https://garden.org/apps/frost-dates/ from the surface of the ground.‚Äù|}}
